```js
const HOST = process.env.HOST || '127.0.0.1';
app.listen(3000, HOST, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on ${HOST}:3000`);
});
```

### 9. ⚙️ Use Environment Variables for Port
Hardcoded ports are a deployment anti-pattern and can expose the app on unintended ports.

```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, ...);
```

